translated: Landström, Adolf Gunnar, district surveyor, Ljungby, born on March 31, 1882 in Jönköping, to Carl Johan L. and Helga Christina Bergström. Married on the 18th with Svea Elvina Ahlberg. Children: Karl-Gustaf, born in 1919, Kerstin Gunhild in 1920, Ebba Elisabet in 1922, Svea Margareta in 1923, Sven-Olof in 1927. Graduated as a surveyor in 1908, cultural technology expert in 1913. District surveyor in Sunnerbo östra district since 1920. Member of the Church Council and Church Board, church warden. Receipient of the Royal Order of Vasa.
